<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ærǧaj"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma">
        <orth>ærǧaj</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>лосось</q>
        </cit>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>salmon</q>
        </cit>
    </sense>
    <re>
        <form type="lemma">
            <orth>ærǧaj fyd</orth>
            <form type="variant">
                <orth>ærǧfyd</orth>
            </form>
        </form>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>бескостное мясо</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>boneless meat</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
    </re>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Непосредственная связь — с <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><lang/><w>arǧej</w><gloss><q>акула</q></gloss></mentioned> (?); ср. также
            <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/><w>irgho: irghonaš</w><gloss><q>порода
            рыбы</q></gloss></mentioned>. Дальнейшие связи ведут к тюркским языкам: <mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>arǧan</w></mentioned> (<bibl><biblScope>%bРадлов I
                296%b</biblScope></bibl>). Ср. д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_læsæg"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The direct relation — with <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><lang/><w>arǧej</w><gloss><q>shark</q></gloss></mentioned> (?); compare also
            <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/><w>irgho: irghonaš</w><gloss><q>fish
            species</q></gloss></mentioned>. The further relations lead to Turkic languages:
            <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>arǧan</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>I 296</biblScope></bibl>). Compare Digor <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_læsæg"/>.</etym>
</entry>
